// place-manor.ipt
// =====================================================================
// A noble's (or wealthy family's) manor house — a household and its
// intrigues. Smaller and more domestic than a castle: no garrison or
// siege-works, but plenty of social machinery — the family, the
// staff, the standing, and the quiet dramas of a great house.
//
// Entry table: [@TF-Manor]
//
// Inputs (optional, via API promptValues):
//   prompt1 town  /  prompt2 shopType (display)  /  prompt3 shopName
//
// Reuses people.ipt. No prices.

Title: Manor
Use: people.ipt

Prompt: town {} an unnamed town
Prompt: shopType {} manor
Prompt: shopName {} 

Table: TF-Manor
Set: town={$prompt1}
Set: passedName={$prompt3}
Set: noble=[@PersonName]
Set: nanc=[@Ancestry]
Set: house=[@FamilyName]
**[@ManorTitle]** *(manor in {$town})*\n&
**[@ManorKind], [@HouseStanding]**\n&
**Head of the house:** [@NobleTitle] {$noble} of House {$house}, a [@PersonDesc] {$nanc} who is [@NobleManner].\n&
**The household:** [@ManorHousehold]\n&
**Also in residence:** [@FamilyMember]\n&
**The talk of the house:** [@HouseTalk]\n&
**{$noble} says:** "[@NobleQuote]"\n&
**Behind closed doors:** [@ManorHook]

Table: ManorTitle
[when]{$passedName}=[do][@ManorName][else]{$passedName}[end]

Table: ManorName
{$house} House
{$house} Manor
The [@ManorNameWord] House
[@ManorNameWord] Hall

Table: ManorNameWord
Ash
Rose
Grey
Elm
Willow
Hart
Laurel
Crane

Table: ManorKind
A grand townhouse at the best address in town
A handsome country manor amid its own gardens and tenant farms
An old family seat, dignified but visibly fraying at the edges
A newly built mansion flaunting freshly minted wealth
A discreet, comfortable house that hides its true wealth well
A sprawling manor far too large for the family that rattles around it

Table: HouseStanding
an old and respected house with deep roots in the region
a rising house whose wealth has outpaced its reputation
a house in quiet decline, trading on a name that still opens doors
the most powerful family in town, and unsubtle about it
a house disgraced a generation ago and clawing its way back
a house whose fortune rests on a single fragile arrangement

Table: NobleTitle
Lord
Lady
Baron
Baroness
Sir
Dame
the Honourable
Master
Mistress

Table: NobleManner
gracious and shrewd, missing nothing behind the courtesy
haughty and exacting, with little patience for inferiors
charming, generous, and quietly drowning in debt
warm and genuinely decent, a rarity among their peers
cold, calculating, and always three moves ahead
nervous and overwhelmed, lately thrust into a role they didn't want
jovial in company and ruthless in private

Table: ManorHousehold
{!n=={6+2d6}}some {$n} staff under [@PersonName], [@StaffStyle]

Table: StaffStyle
a steward who has served the house for decades and knows every secret
a new steward still earning the staff's trust
a household quietly loyal beyond mere wages
servants who gossip freely the moment the family's backs are turned
a skeleton staff stretched thin to keep up appearances
staff divided in loyalty between rival members of the family

Table: FamilyMember
{!fm==[@PersonName]}{!fanc==[@Ancestry]}{$fm}, a [@PersonDesc] {$fanc} — [@FamilyRole], [@FamilyTrouble]

Table: FamilyRole
the heir, groomed for a position they may not want
a younger sibling resentful of being overlooked
the matriarch (or patriarch), officially retired and actually in charge
a cousin staying "temporarily" for far too long
a spouse who married in and is still treated as an outsider
a ward or hostage of another house, watched and courted
the family disappointment, kept quietly out of sight

Table: FamilyTrouble
deep in a romance the family would never approve
gambling away money the house cannot spare
secretly negotiating with a rival house
hiding a scandal that could ruin them all
the only one who sees the danger the family is ignoring
plotting, with patience, to take control of the house

Table: HouseTalk
an advantageous marriage is being arranged, willing or not
a grand feast or ball is days away and the house is in uproar
an inheritance dispute simmers beneath every polite dinner
the family's finances are far worse than anyone admits aloud
a long-absent relative has written to announce their return
a servant was dismissed suddenly, and no one will say why

Table: NobleQuote
You'll forgive the formality. A house like ours is always watched.
State your business plainly; I've little time for those who don't.
We reward loyalty handsomely. We remember the other kind, too.
Whatever you've heard about this family, the truth is more interesting.
I am the soul of hospitality — until I have reason not to be.
Discretion is the only currency that never loses its value here.
Everyone wants something from a house like this. What's your price?

Table: ManorHook
the head of the house is quietly hiring outsiders for a delicate matter
a family heirloom has been stolen, and they suspect one of their own
the noble is being blackmailed over a secret that would ruin the house
two branches of the family are at war over the succession
a guest in the house is not who they claim to be
the house's wealth comes from a source that must never come to light
someone in the household has been poisoning the noble, slowly
the family is sheltering a fugitive of high birth
a marriage alliance is collapsing and threatening to take allies with it
the noble has made a bargain with a dangerous party and can't pay the price

// Standalone manor name (sets the house surname first).
Table: TF-ManorName
{!house==[@FamilyName]}[@ManorName]
